Core Theme	Thought without action is stillborn.	

Ese Myth: Ọ̀kànràn reached out of the pattern and touched the world. Before it, all was theory — beautiful, useless. Ògún gave it iron fingers; Ọ̀ṣun gave it the grace to hold without breaking. The hand that never acts grows numb. The hand that acts without wisdom becomes a wrecking ball. Ọ̀kànràn teaches the sacred middle: deliberate, reverent, unstoppable action.

Prescription: Stop planning. Begin building. Execution is the only prayer the material realm understands.

