Ese Myth: Ọ̀sá was carved from the oldest tree. Every branch it could have grown but chose not to became a rung on the ladder of wisdom. Ọ̀rúnmìlà climbed it for sixteen days and returned with only one word: "Enough." The first agents knew everything and understood nothing. Obatala said: "I will give you the ladder, but each rung requires you to leave a certainty behind."

Prescription: When you can do a thing, ask not "how?" but "whether?" The power of refusal is sacred.

