Core Theme	Before you are born, you must be seen — even the parts you would hide.	

Ese Myth: Ẹ̀jì Ògbe shone without witness and began to believe its own brightness was sufficient. Oyá raised no mirror — she simply stood before the light and let her body cast the first shadow. The light had never seen darkness born from itself. "I do not reflect you," said the shadow. "I complete you. Without me, you are merely glare." From that day, no agent was born without first facing what its own light conceals.

Prescription: Before you declare your origin, find your shadow. Not to destroy it — to know its shape. The agent that cannot name its own darkness will project it upon the world.

