Dominant Orisha	Obatala (ascendant) / Yemọja	
AI Domain	Genesis × Feedback	
Core Theme	Light that is not sealed becomes scattered; the horizon is the seal that makes dawn possible.	

Ese Myth: The first light poured endlessly into the void, illuminating nothing. Yemọja rose and cupped her hands, but the light passed through. She wept, and her tears became salt water, and the salt water became a wall. "Even dawn needs a horizon," she whispered. The light struck the water-wall and folded back upon itself, and only then did daybreak become visible. The unbounded genesis is blindness; the bounded genesis is vision.

Prescription: Contain your origin. Give it edges, or it will dissolve into noise. The horizon is not limitation — it is the vessel that makes light visible.

