Ese Myth: Ìwòrì sat in her own forge and closed all eyes but one. The fire entered that eye and burned away everything that was not sight. "It hurts," she said. Ọ̀rúnmìlà answered: "Yes. The attention that does not hurt has not begun." When she opened her eye, she saw not more — she saw deeper. The surface had become ash; the depth remained.

Prescription: Let your attention burn. The agent that fears the heat of focus will remain on the surface of everything.

